1
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:04,266
[♪]

2
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:09,133
What's going on? Who's there?
Where am I?

3
00:01:09,166 --> 00:01:11,666
If anyone can hear me,

4
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:13,633
take me to the Moon Tower!

5
00:01:13,666 --> 00:01:18,266
It's that robot Astro's fault
that I'm stuck in here!

6
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:21,366
Huh?

7
00:01:26,466 --> 00:01:28,266
It can't be!

8
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:30,800
I am the energy source

9
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:33,566
that governs the secrets
of the universe.

10
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:36,266
The ancient people
called me "Firebird."

11
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:39,566
Please, Firebird,
I know you can help me

12
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:41,433
if you would just
tell me the secrets.

13
00:01:41,466 --> 00:01:45,033
Those who seek the knowledge
must invoke the door of wisdom.

14
00:01:45,066 --> 00:01:47,266
If you possess
the qualifications,

15
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:49,266
the Moon Tower will appear
and the door will open.

16
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:52,133
Take me to the tower,
Firebird!

17
00:01:52,166 --> 00:01:54,400
I want to possess
the secrets of the universe.

18
00:01:54,433 --> 00:01:57,633
If you are worthy
of the secrets,

19
00:01:57,666 --> 00:02:01,800
they will find
their way to you.

20
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:05,533
What is revealed inside
the door of wisdom

21
00:02:05,566 --> 00:02:10,666
will be determined
by your motives.

22
00:02:10,700 --> 00:02:14,700
Choose your actions
carefully!

23
00:02:14,733 --> 00:02:18,033
[SCREAMING]

24
00:02:39,366 --> 00:02:41,233
[GRUNTS]

25
00:02:41,266 --> 00:02:42,300
Huh?

26
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:44,433
Where am I?

27
00:02:46,266 --> 00:02:47,500
If Firebird thinks
I'm going to wait

28
00:02:47,533 --> 00:02:49,500
until the secrets find me...

29
00:02:49,533 --> 00:02:51,700
FIREBIRD: <i>If you are worthy</i>
<i>of the secrets,</i>

30
00:02:51,733 --> 00:02:54,233
<i>they will find</i>
<i>their way to you.</i>

31
00:02:54,266 --> 00:02:57,200
...then she's got
another think coming.

32
00:02:57,233 --> 00:03:00,666
In no time, I'll be ruling
the entire world.

33
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:04,233
But first I have to make it
to that Moon Tower door.

34
00:03:04,266 --> 00:03:06,633
This time nothing's
going to get in my way!

35
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:20,633
O'SHAY: The Moon Tower
has disappeared?

36
00:03:22,433 --> 00:03:25,333
Just when I was putting together
the investigation team.

37
00:03:25,366 --> 00:03:26,333
Huh?

38
00:03:29,766 --> 00:03:32,466
[SCREAMING]

39
00:03:37,566 --> 00:03:40,133
Doctor, do you think
someone as evil as Rock

40
00:03:40,166 --> 00:03:41,766
would carry around
a picture of his mother?

41
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,366
Hmm.

42
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,366
It does seem strange.

43
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:50,166
[COMMUNICATOR RINGS]

44
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:52,433
<i>So nice to see you again,</i>
<i>doctor.</i>

45
00:03:52,466 --> 00:03:56,033
Huh? Five more minutes and
I'd have been in my pajamas.

46
00:03:56,066 --> 00:03:57,533
<i>I have uncovered</i>

47
00:03:57,566 --> 00:03:59,800
some very important information
<i>about Rock.</i>

48
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:01,566
Rock? What did you find?

49
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,733
<i>Something very interesting.</i>

50
00:04:03,766 --> 00:04:05,400
<i>The man grew up at a facility</i>

51
00:04:05,433 --> 00:04:07,566
<i>designed to research</i>
<i>psychic power.</i>

52
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,366
Is this some kind of joke?

53
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:11,300
<i>Rock was born with the ability</i>

54
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:13,733
<i>to control other people</i>
<i>with his mind.</i>

55
00:04:13,766 --> 00:04:17,266
<i>Hurry now! There's not</i>
<i>a single moment to lose!</i>

56
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:18,533
<i>Oh, it's past my bedtime.</i>

57
00:04:18,566 --> 00:04:21,033
<i>I'll call you first thing</i>
<i>in the morning, doctor.</i>

58
00:04:21,066 --> 00:04:23,166
And I was hoping
to sleep in.

59
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,166
[SIGHS]

60
00:04:29,233 --> 00:04:30,800
Driver, step on it,
will you?

61
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:32,166
I'm in a hurry.

62
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:35,733
We'll be there soon,
Mr. Deputy Chairman.

63
00:04:35,766 --> 00:04:39,133
Everything will be...just fine.

64
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:44,166
SECRETARY:
He's here, sir.

65
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,366
Come in, come in.

66
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,600
Deputy Chairman,
nice to see you!

67
00:04:53,433 --> 00:04:55,133
O'SHAY:
Well, hello, Chairman Lyon.

68
00:04:55,166 --> 00:04:56,600
What can we do for you?

69
00:04:56,633 --> 00:04:58,466
<i>Good morning,</i>
<i>Dr. O'Shay.</i>

70
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:00,600
<i>My apologies</i>
<i>for such short notice,</i>

71
00:05:00,633 --> 00:05:02,400
<i>but I have an extremely</i>
<i>urgent request.</i>

72
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:04,333
My goodness, chairman.

73
00:05:04,366 --> 00:05:07,100
Are the city sewer-bots
acting up again?

74
00:05:07,133 --> 00:05:08,300
<i>Worse than that.</i>

75
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:10,133
<i>I'm sending you to an island.</i>

76
00:05:10,166 --> 00:05:12,300
Did I do something wrong?

77
00:05:12,333 --> 00:05:15,266
<i>No, no, doctor. Of course not.</i>

78
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,366
<i>I need you to investigate</i>

79
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:18,366
<i>a strange occurrence</i>
<i>on Phoenix Island.</i>

80
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:20,133
Oh.

81
00:05:20,166 --> 00:05:21,700
What's on
Phoenix Island, doctor?

82
00:05:21,733 --> 00:05:24,100
Ruins of
an ancient civilization

83
00:05:24,133 --> 00:05:26,500
who, according to legend,
possessed psychic powers.

84
00:05:26,533 --> 00:05:29,066
It's baffled scientists
for years.

85
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,200
LYON:
<i>The people worshipped</i>

86
00:05:30,233 --> 00:05:32,500
<i>a mysterious creature</i>
<i>called "Firebird."</i>

87
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:33,633
<i>The creature gave them</i>

88
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:36,066
<i>the ability</i>
<i>to communicate telepathically.</i>

89
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:38,333
<i>They could even move objects</i>
<i>with their minds</i>

90
00:05:38,366 --> 00:05:39,633
<i>using telekinesis,</i>

91
00:05:39,666 --> 00:05:43,033
<i>which is how they built</i>
<i>their tremendous buildings.</i>

92
00:05:43,066 --> 00:05:46,166
<i>But recent unexplained</i>
<i>electromagnetic waves</i>

93
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,500
<i>appear to be coming</i>
<i>from the island.</i>

94
00:05:47,533 --> 00:05:49,166
<i>We have no idea</i>
<i>what you'll find there</i>

95
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,033
<i>and it could be dangerous.</i>

96
00:05:51,066 --> 00:05:52,766
<i>I'm sure you'll want</i>
<i>to take Astro with you.</i>

97
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,400
Of course, chairman.

98
00:05:54,433 --> 00:05:56,466
Astro and I will get
to the bottom of this.

99
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:58,100
<i>Please conduct</i>
<i>this investigation</i>

100
00:05:58,133 --> 00:06:00,166
<i>with the utmost secrecy.</i>

101
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:03,466
<i>I'm sure you know, doctor,</i>
<i>how quickly people can panic.</i>

102
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:05,266
<i>So good luck.</i>

103
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:07,633
A top-secret mission.

104
00:06:07,666 --> 00:06:09,133
Mm-hm.

105
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:13,166
Eh? What?

106
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:16,133
I haven't the vaguest idea
who I was just talking to.

107
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:30,366
Well, that puts Astro
into the mix, now, doesn't it?

108
00:06:36,466 --> 00:06:39,600
Hello, Dr. O'Shay.
My name is Professor Atami.

109
00:06:39,633 --> 00:06:41,366
Chairman Lyon
has asked me to join

110
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,433
your special
investigation team.

111
00:06:43,466 --> 00:06:47,166
Professor!
So nice to meet you, finally.

112
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,666
I must say, your excellent
reputation precedes you.

113
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:57,500
MAN: There's an emergency call
for Dr. O'Shay.

114
00:06:57,533 --> 00:06:59,366
Put it through, please.

115
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:02,233
<i>Hello, Dr. O'Shay.</i>

116
00:07:02,266 --> 00:07:03,533
<i>Pardon the interruption,</i>

117
00:07:03,566 --> 00:07:05,633
<i>but I wanted to update you</i>
<i>with my latest findings.</i>

118
00:07:05,666 --> 00:07:08,366
O'SHAY: Do you have
more information about Rock?

119
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:10,200
Yes, apparently
something known as

120
00:07:10,233 --> 00:07:12,100
the Psychic Power
Research Institute

121
00:07:12,133 --> 00:07:14,200
obtained custody of him
when he was very young

122
00:07:14,233 --> 00:07:16,100
and he received
extensive psychic training

123
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:17,166
throughout his childhood.

124
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:19,600
Extensive psychic training?

125
00:07:19,633 --> 00:07:21,700
KISAGARI: <i>They sought</i>
<i>only very bright children</i>

126
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:25,100
<i>appearing to have</i>
<i>unusually high levels of ESP,</i>

127
00:07:25,133 --> 00:07:26,400
<i>extrasensory perception,</i>

128
00:07:26,433 --> 00:07:31,066
<i>then held them captive</i>
<i>for testing.</i>

129
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:33,366
I can't believe any scientist

130
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:36,066
would allow such
inhumane treatment.

131
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:37,166
Not only that, but it's rumored

132
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:39,400
<i>that they were</i>
<i>brainwashing the children</i>

133
00:07:39,433 --> 00:07:41,633
<i>in a plot to overthrow</i>
<i>the government.</i>

134
00:07:41,666 --> 00:07:43,800
<i>Interestingly,</i>
<i>Rock escaped from the facility</i>

135
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:45,366
<i>when he was 12 years old.</i>

136
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,100
Mr. Kisagari,

137
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:49,600
did you find out anything more
about the locket?

138
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:54,300
<i>He wore that locket the entire</i>
<i>time he was at the institute.</i>

139
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:57,633
And he's probably
worn it ever since.

140
00:07:57,666 --> 00:07:59,500
<i>Strange thing about it is</i>

141
00:07:59,533 --> 00:08:02,533
the locket was apparently empty
while he was at the institute.

142
00:08:03,411 --> 00:08:05,011
Huh?
Empty?

143
00:08:05,045 --> 00:08:06,411
<i>We need more answers,</i>

144
00:08:06,445 --> 00:08:08,511
<i>and I'll be in touch</i>
<i>as soon as I have some.</i>

145
00:08:08,545 --> 00:08:10,045
<i>Goodbye.</i>

146
00:08:10,078 --> 00:08:12,545
If it was empty
when he was at the facility,

147
00:08:12,578 --> 00:08:15,478
then whose photograph
is in it now?

148
00:08:15,511 --> 00:08:18,111
ASTRO: I don't know,
but it must be important.

149
00:08:18,145 --> 00:08:19,578
Why else would he wear it?

150
00:08:22,478 --> 00:08:23,945
[GRUNTS]

151
00:08:23,978 --> 00:08:26,311
ROCK:
<i>What would they know?</i>

152
00:08:47,245 --> 00:08:48,978
The Phoenix Island ruins.

153
00:08:49,011 --> 00:08:51,211
ASTRO: They must have used
telekinesis.

154
00:08:51,245 --> 00:08:53,945
How else could they build that?

155
00:08:53,978 --> 00:08:56,545
O'SHAY: Quite
an advanced civilization.

156
00:08:58,311 --> 00:09:00,511
This way! The entrance
is over here!

157
00:09:00,545 --> 00:09:03,478
ALL:
Oh!

158
00:09:08,945 --> 00:09:10,211
Astro, would you
make sure it's safe?

159
00:09:10,245 --> 00:09:12,611
Okay, professor.

160
00:09:19,311 --> 00:09:20,611
Just be careful, Astro!

161
00:09:20,645 --> 00:09:22,445
ATAMI:
Team!

162
00:09:22,478 --> 00:09:24,245
I've found something strange
on these walls.

163
00:09:24,278 --> 00:09:26,178
Huh?

164
00:09:33,645 --> 00:09:37,145
I wonder what
these pillars are for?

165
00:09:37,178 --> 00:09:40,111
O'SHAY: This chamber
does look rather unusual.

166
00:09:40,145 --> 00:09:42,411
Take a close look
at the markings.

167
00:09:42,445 --> 00:09:44,645
They're like nothing
I've ever seen before.

168
00:09:44,678 --> 00:09:45,878
How fascinating!

169
00:09:45,911 --> 00:09:47,611
MAN: Some kind
of ancient language.

170
00:09:47,645 --> 00:09:48,611
WOMAN: This room's
a little creepy.

171
00:09:49,911 --> 00:09:52,045
[MACHINE WHIRS]

172
00:09:55,178 --> 00:09:56,211
ALL:
Huh?

173
00:09:58,978 --> 00:10:00,245
O'SHAY:
What? Hey!

174
00:10:00,278 --> 00:10:03,278
[ALL GASP]

175
00:10:03,311 --> 00:10:04,878
Let us out of here!

176
00:10:04,911 --> 00:10:06,978
What are you up to?

177
00:10:07,011 --> 00:10:10,078
Welcome to the ancient
Phoenix Island prison

178
00:10:10,111 --> 00:10:12,311
where victims were held
against their will.

179
00:10:12,345 --> 00:10:13,545
What are you talking about?

180
00:10:15,345 --> 00:10:18,211
<i>Chairman Lyon will have</i>
<i>your hide for this.</i>

181
00:10:18,245 --> 00:10:19,478
Dr. O'Shay needs my help!

182
00:10:21,578 --> 00:10:22,978
[GRUNTING]

183
00:10:27,445 --> 00:10:29,145
Gotta be quicker than that, pal!

184
00:10:29,178 --> 00:10:30,411
Psych!

185
00:10:30,445 --> 00:10:33,178
Hey, Stoneface,
chill with the lasers!

186
00:10:35,478 --> 00:10:37,045
[GRUNTS]

187
00:10:37,078 --> 00:10:39,445
Professor Atami,
why are you doing this?

188
00:10:39,478 --> 00:10:41,378
You'll see soon enough.

189
00:10:41,411 --> 00:10:42,878
ASTRO: Doctor!
Huh?

190
00:10:44,945 --> 00:10:47,111
Professor Atami,
what's going on here?

191
00:10:47,145 --> 00:10:50,078
Perhaps you should call me
by my real name, Astro.

192
00:10:50,111 --> 00:10:51,845
Wait. I've heard
that voice before.

193
00:10:53,578 --> 00:10:55,145
ASTRO:
Rock!

194
00:10:55,178 --> 00:10:57,645
I thought you were stuck
in that warp tunnel forever!

195
00:10:57,678 --> 00:11:00,311
Let's just say a friend
sent me back on a mission.

196
00:11:01,445 --> 00:11:03,111
ASTRO: Huh?

197
00:11:03,145 --> 00:11:04,178
[BOTH GASP]

198
00:11:04,211 --> 00:11:06,545
What is that?
Just stop!

199
00:11:06,578 --> 00:11:09,111
One more step and your friends
will be burned to a crisp!

200
00:11:09,145 --> 00:11:10,445
[GROWLS]

201
00:11:10,478 --> 00:11:12,178
Pay attention, Astro!

202
00:11:12,211 --> 00:11:14,045
You will use the power
on this island

203
00:11:14,078 --> 00:11:16,378
to enable me to finally
access the Moon Tower!

204
00:11:16,411 --> 00:11:18,378
That's impossible!

205
00:11:18,411 --> 00:11:22,345
ROCK: This temple is like a
giant dimensional transmitter.

206
00:11:22,378 --> 00:11:25,011
When you combine
your electronic brain energy

207
00:11:25,045 --> 00:11:27,145
with the psychic power
of these ruins,

208
00:11:27,178 --> 00:11:29,878
you should be able to summon
the Moon Tower to Earth.

209
00:11:29,911 --> 00:11:32,478
But you have no idea
of the consequences

210
00:11:32,511 --> 00:11:33,845
of combining all that energy!

211
00:11:39,378 --> 00:11:41,245
Here, Rock. Take a look at this!

212
00:11:41,278 --> 00:11:43,411
Huh?

213
00:11:43,445 --> 00:11:46,445
The woman in this picture must
mean something special to you.

214
00:11:46,478 --> 00:11:50,278
Think back to the time
when you were with your family.

215
00:11:50,311 --> 00:11:52,611
[LAUGHS]

216
00:11:52,645 --> 00:11:55,011
Well, what's wrong?

217
00:11:55,045 --> 00:11:58,478
That's a fake picture I used
back in my days as a con man!

218
00:11:58,511 --> 00:12:00,645
I cut it out from an ad
in a magazine.

219
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:02,945
I don't even know
who she is!

220
00:12:02,978 --> 00:12:04,311
Huh?

221
00:12:04,345 --> 00:12:07,911
I never cared for anyone
and no one ever cared for me,

222
00:12:07,945 --> 00:12:09,211
not even my parents,

223
00:12:09,245 --> 00:12:11,145
who freaked out when they
realized I was different

224
00:12:11,178 --> 00:12:13,145
and then put me
in that crazy facility.

225
00:12:13,178 --> 00:12:14,511
But, Rock...

226
00:12:17,078 --> 00:12:19,011
[GASPS]

227
00:12:19,045 --> 00:12:20,645
So are you going
to help me, Astro,

228
00:12:20,678 --> 00:12:22,311
or do you want
to see them vaporized?

229
00:12:22,345 --> 00:12:24,911
No, stop!

230
00:12:24,945 --> 00:12:26,345
I'll help you
get the Moon Tower.

231
00:12:26,378 --> 00:12:28,211
But, Astro--

232
00:12:28,245 --> 00:12:30,411
Well, then, we'd better
get to it, my robot friend.

233
00:12:30,445 --> 00:12:31,611
Time's a-wasting.

234
00:12:36,245 --> 00:12:37,211
[MACHINE WHIRRS]

235
00:12:41,311 --> 00:12:44,078
[GRUNTS]

236
00:12:44,111 --> 00:12:45,178
Huh?

237
00:12:53,945 --> 00:12:55,078
[ALL GASP]

238
00:13:00,111 --> 00:13:01,278
[SCREAMING]

239
00:13:12,645 --> 00:13:14,545
Look! It really is
the Moon Tower!

240
00:13:25,578 --> 00:13:27,111
[SCREAMING]

241
00:13:37,111 --> 00:13:38,345
[ALL GASP]

242
00:13:38,378 --> 00:13:39,478
[LAUGHS]

243
00:13:44,078 --> 00:13:47,045
Good job, Astro.

244
00:13:47,078 --> 00:13:48,978
Oh, no! Astro!

245
00:13:54,511 --> 00:13:56,645
Huh?

246
00:13:56,678 --> 00:14:00,345
[GRUNTING]

247
00:14:01,578 --> 00:14:03,145
Astro's okay!

248
00:14:03,178 --> 00:14:04,478
[GRUNTS]

249
00:14:07,978 --> 00:14:11,111
Now the time has finally come
to unlock the secrets.

250
00:14:12,645 --> 00:14:13,845
[SCREAMING]

251
00:14:15,645 --> 00:14:17,111
[ALL PANTING]

252
00:14:24,145 --> 00:14:26,045
What's happening
inside the tower? Huh?

253
00:14:26,078 --> 00:14:27,411
[COMMUNICATOR BEEPS]

254
00:14:29,678 --> 00:14:31,245
<i>Doctor, are you all right?</i>

255
00:14:31,278 --> 00:14:33,278
We're okay, Detective Tawashi.

256
00:14:33,311 --> 00:14:35,445
<i>We found the real</i>
<i>Professor Atami</i>

257
00:14:35,478 --> 00:14:37,245
<i>and figured</i>
<i>you might be in trouble.</i>

258
00:14:37,278 --> 00:14:39,511
<i>We're headed your way</i>
<i>right now.</i>

259
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:42,878
<i>Doctor, I found out</i>
<i>why Rock's locket was empty</i>

260
00:14:42,911 --> 00:14:44,578
<i>while he was</i>
<i>at the psychic institute.</i>

261
00:14:44,611 --> 00:14:47,278
<i>All of the children's</i>
<i>family photos were confiscated</i>

262
00:14:47,311 --> 00:14:49,411
<i>to suppress</i>
<i>their childhood memories.</i>

263
00:14:49,445 --> 00:14:51,978
<i>That way, they were easier</i>
<i>to brainwash.</i>

264
00:14:52,011 --> 00:14:54,478
What a terribly
cruel thing to do.

265
00:14:54,511 --> 00:14:59,278
<i>However, I did find</i>
<i>a picture of Rock's mother.</i>

266
00:14:59,311 --> 00:15:02,278
Oh?
Hey, compare it to the locket!

267
00:15:03,545 --> 00:15:05,578
She is different.

268
00:15:05,611 --> 00:15:06,578
[BOTH SCREAM]

269
00:15:10,678 --> 00:15:12,245
[SCREAMS]

270
00:15:12,278 --> 00:15:14,211
My hand!

271
00:15:14,245 --> 00:15:15,111
I can't get it off!

272
00:15:19,045 --> 00:15:21,245
[GROANS]

273
00:15:25,545 --> 00:15:27,511
The Moon Tower!
It's starting to rise!

274
00:15:31,311 --> 00:15:33,078
The tower's flying
back up into the air!

275
00:15:44,145 --> 00:15:46,511
I gotta go find Rock
and help him, doctor.

276
00:15:46,545 --> 00:15:48,011
But, Astro--

277
00:15:56,678 --> 00:15:58,311
Rock, hang on!

278
00:15:59,578 --> 00:16:02,045
[SCREAMING]

279
00:16:12,111 --> 00:16:12,911
Astro!

280
00:16:14,978 --> 00:16:17,411
[GROANING]

281
00:16:17,445 --> 00:16:18,578
Rock, stop!

282
00:16:18,611 --> 00:16:20,378
[GRUNTS]

283
00:16:20,411 --> 00:16:21,545
[GROANS]

284
00:16:24,611 --> 00:16:28,145
[GRUNTS]

285
00:16:28,178 --> 00:16:31,345
[SCREAMS]

286
00:16:31,378 --> 00:16:36,611
FIREBIRD: The door of wisdom
is closed to an evil heart.

287
00:16:36,645 --> 00:16:38,345
Your use of this knowledge

288
00:16:38,378 --> 00:16:42,911
would only bring about
destruction and ruin.

289
00:16:45,145 --> 00:16:48,211
Rock, look at this!

290
00:16:48,245 --> 00:16:49,178
You've gotta have
some memories

291
00:16:49,211 --> 00:16:51,478
from before you went
to that psychic place.

292
00:16:51,511 --> 00:16:53,145
[SCREAMS]

293
00:16:53,178 --> 00:16:57,145
Think back, Rock.
Where did you get this?

294
00:17:02,278 --> 00:17:03,045
Rock, stop it!

295
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:10,978
[BOTH GROANING]

296
00:17:12,578 --> 00:17:14,211
Whoa! Whooaah!

297
00:17:14,245 --> 00:17:18,011
[BOTH SCREAMING]

298
00:17:27,511 --> 00:17:29,945
Rock!

299
00:17:32,278 --> 00:17:33,545
Take this!

300
00:17:33,578 --> 00:17:35,245
[SCREAMS]

301
00:17:35,278 --> 00:17:37,078
[SIGHS]

302
00:18:04,311 --> 00:18:05,378
Mother.

303
00:18:11,478 --> 00:18:14,645
Rock, this is for you.

304
00:18:14,678 --> 00:18:17,345
I wish I could be with you,
darling, but I can't.

305
00:18:17,378 --> 00:18:18,978
Not anymore.

306
00:18:19,011 --> 00:18:22,378
But I promise I'll always
be watching over you.

307
00:18:32,478 --> 00:18:33,345
[ALL GASP]

308
00:18:41,645 --> 00:18:43,978
Is that...Firebird?

309
00:18:44,011 --> 00:18:48,478
Your kind will not benefit
from the universal secrets

310
00:18:48,511 --> 00:18:52,511
unless the knowledge is
entrusted to a worthy recipient.

311
00:18:52,545 --> 00:18:57,045
I will wait
until that day comes.

312
00:19:17,178 --> 00:19:19,611
[SIGHS]

313
00:19:20,945 --> 00:19:22,311
[SIGHS]

314
00:19:22,345 --> 00:19:23,311
Oh!

315
00:19:26,911 --> 00:19:28,445
Watch out!

316
00:19:28,478 --> 00:19:30,245
Rock!

317
00:19:38,111 --> 00:19:40,311
Phew!

318
00:19:49,578 --> 00:19:51,578
KISAGARI: Rock's parents
sent him to the facility

319
00:19:51,611 --> 00:19:55,278
because they were told
it was best for him.

320
00:19:55,311 --> 00:19:57,478
But, sadly, the people
at the facility

321
00:19:57,511 --> 00:20:00,245
made him believe that his
parents had abandoned him.

322
00:20:00,278 --> 00:20:03,045
Be careful! That man has
dangerous psychic powers.

323
00:20:03,078 --> 00:20:04,311
He can manipulate people.

324
00:20:04,345 --> 00:20:06,511
[LAUGHS]

325
00:20:06,545 --> 00:20:09,245
Don't worry, I don't have
that power anymore.

326
00:20:13,078 --> 00:20:16,045
Doctor, do you
think that Rock

327
00:20:16,078 --> 00:20:18,245
will be able to start
a new life?

328
00:20:18,278 --> 00:20:20,978
With your help, Astro,
I think he will.

329
00:20:32,511 --> 00:20:34,245
[♪]

